Package: persephone
Title: Agent-Based Model for Simulating Skeletal Lesion Formation and Mortality in Archaeological Populations
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: c(
    person("Amy", "Anderson", , "Amy.Anderson-1@colorado.edu", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Michael Holton", "Price", role = "ctb"),
    person("Nicolas", "Gauthier", role = "ctb"),
    person("Bret", "Beheim", role = "ctb")
    )
Description: An agent-based model (ABM) for simulating skeletal assemblage
    data in bioarchaeology. Individuals in a birth cohort face annual risks of
    skeletal lesion formation and age-specific mortality following a Siler
    hazard model. Lesion status can modify mortality risk, enabling
    exploration of the osteological paradox and evaluation of survival
    analysis methods applied to cemetery data.
